Continuous data was checked for assumptions of normality. There are different ways to calculate growth with a linear model (Lugert et al, 2016), and in order to find the best model we tested the following: 

Absolute growth (AG): \( W_t - W_i \); Absolute growth rate (AGR):\( \frac{W_t - W_i}{t} \); 
Relative growth rate (RGR):  \( \left( \frac{W_t - W_i}{W_i} \right) \times 100 \); Instantaneous growth rate (IGR): \( \frac{\log W_t - \log W_i}{t} \); 
Specific growth rate(SGR):\(\frac{(\log W_t - \log W_i)}{t} \times 100\); 
Thermal unit growth concept (TGC): \(\frac{W_t^{\frac{1}{3}} - W_i^{\frac{1}{3}}}{\sum T_{\text{ef}}}\); where Wt is the final forklength and Wi is the initial forklength (Lugert et al 2014) and ∑Tef = Sum of daily effective temperature = n(Temp - Minimum temperature for growth) (See McCormick et al 1972); n = period of time in days. Additionally, we adjusted those rates that include time to account for the difference between summer and winter days, removing the latter: wher Summer absolute growth rate (SAGR): \( \frac{W_t - W_i}{t - winter days} \); Summer instantaneous growth rate (SIGR): \( \frac{\log W_t - \log W_i}{t - winter days} \); Summer specific growth rate (SSGR):\(\frac{(\log W_t - \log W_i)}{t - winter days} \times 100\); Summer thermal unit growth concept (STGC): \(\frac{W_t^{\frac{1}{3}} - W_i^{\frac{1}{3}}}{\sum T_{\text{ef}}}\)

First, iterations through linear regression models with each growth model were used to test which growth model fit best our data using the function 'lm' with base R package (cite r):

Growth ~ condition + size at release + year of release + site of release + distance moved (didn't include temperature as it is included in the Thermal Unit Growth model)

The best growth equation was chosen based on the calculated best r-squared/MPD values (highest/lowest). Next, iterations using the function 'dredge', library MuMln (Bartón, 2020) were run with the full model and the chosen dependent growth rate variable. 

Full model run: Growth ~ condition + size at release + year of release + site of release + distance moved + summer temperature

## Results

```{r warning = FALSE}

growth_year1 <- mydata_first %>%
  arrange(IndividualID, EHYear_Extracted) %>%
  group_by(IndividualID) %>%
  reframe(
    # ABSOLUTE GROWTH
    AG = ForkLength_mm[2] - ForkLength_mm[1],
    # ABSOLUTE GROWTH RATE
    AGR = (ForkLength_mm[2] - ForkLength_mm [1])/ (day[2] - day [1]),
    AGR_summer_days = (ForkLength_mm[2] - ForkLength_mm [1])/ (summer_days),
    AGR_winter_days = (ForkLength_mm[2] - ForkLength_mm [1])/ (day[2] - day [1]- winter_days),
    # RELATIVE GROWTH RATE
    RGR = ((ForkLength_mm[2] - ForkLength_mm [1])/ForkLength_mm [1])*100,
    # INSTANTANEOUS GROWTH RATE
    IGR = (log(ForkLength_mm[2]) - log(ForkLength_mm [1]))/ (day[2] - day [1]),
    IGR_summer_days = (log(ForkLength_mm[2]) - log(ForkLength_mm [1]))/ (summer_days),
    IGR_winter_days = (log(ForkLength_mm[2]) - log(ForkLength_mm [1]))/ (day[2] - day [1] - winter_days),
    IGR_mod = 100 * (log(ForkLength_mm[2] /ForkLength_mm [1])) / (day[2] - day [1]),
    # SPECIFIC GROWTH RATE
    SGR = ((log(ForkLength_mm[2]) - log(ForkLength_mm [1]))/ day[2] - (day [1]))*100,
    SGR_summer_days = ((log(ForkLength_mm[2]) - log(ForkLength_mm [1]))/ summer_days)*100,
    SGR_winter_days = ((log(ForkLength_mm[2]) - log(ForkLength_mm [1]))/ day[2] - (day [1] - winter_days))*100,
    # THERMAL GROWTH COEFFICIENT
    TGC = calculate_tgc (ForkLength_mm[2], ForkLength_mm[1], summer_days, winter_days, GrowthTemperatureBack, GrowthTemperatureOut),
    # SUMMER THERMAL GROWTH COEFFICIENT
    STGC = calculate_stgc (ForkLength_mm[2], ForkLength_mm[1], summer_days, winter_days, GrowthTemperatureBack, GrowthTemperatureOut), 
    # temp OF RELEASE 
    summer_temp = GrowthTemperatureBack [1],
    # day
    day = day,
    # size at release
    release_fl = release_fl [1] ,
    # condition
    condition = Condition [1],
    # release year
    release_year =release_year [1],
    # distance moved
    distance_moved = distance_moved [2],
