The best growth model was IGR (table 4; R-squared:  0.2895,	Adjusted R-squared:  0.2862, F-statistic: 87.87,  p-value: < 2.2e-16). Fish grew at an average instantaneous growth rate of 2.279299×10−4, although among these 250 fish presented and average negative growth of 5.24mm. The minimum observed change in forklenght was detected for an individual fish that shrank 48mm (lowest IGR = -1.064) after 351 days released with group 6 (Deemer) in 2021 and recaptured at 2.757 km from where it was originally released. The maximum observed change in forklenght was 119 mm for an individual fish caught after 350 days released with group 4 (Gypsy Pools) in 2022 and recaptured at 157 meters from where it was originally released. The maximum IGR was 2.385806×10−3 for an individual fish released in 2019 (forklenght at release 88mm) with group 5 (X), and recaptured after 327 days having displaced 174 meters.


